<br>
I was making a run through EC today to pay off a debt to a guildmate.  An auction catches my eye.  I send the seller a tell, asking how much they're asking for said item.  They respond, &quot;make offer,&quot; and I do so.  They say, &quot;okay, that'll be enough&quot; and tell me that they have to run some errands on their current character first, and then they'll be on with the character that has the item.  Okay, fine.  I need some time to run to the bank, anyway.  I go the bank, and come back in EC, and I see him auctioning the item again.  Strange, I think, but maybe they're not lore and he has a few of them to sell.  No problem.<br>
<br>
So, I wait.  And I wait.  About 30 minutes goes by, and I finally do a /who on the guy to see if he's still around, and nope, he's not on, so I figure he's logged onto his other character.  I wait a few more minutes, and finally see another character selling the same item.  &quot;Hmm,&quot; I think, and send this other character a tell, asking if he's the same person I spoke to earlier about the item.  He says yes.  So I ask him if we're still on for the deal.  He says &quot;one sec.&quot;  So I wait again.  And wait some more.  And after 10 minutes I see him auctioning the item, only this time, he's selling it for 700pp more than what I originally offered, and taking higher bids.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :/ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":/"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   To put it bluntly, I was pretty pissed.<br>
<br>
Now, I'm not one to try to tell someone how they can auction off their items, but for Christ's sake, if you agree to sell something to someone, don't go back and make them waste nearly an hour just so you can make a few extra bucks, especially if you don't even bother sending them a tell to let them know what's going on.  Had I been told up front that he'd continue to auction the item until the price didn't go any higher, I would've said &quot;no thanks&quot; and logged, since that's what I planning to do anyway.  It didn't occur to me that &quot;okay, that'll be enough&quot; could also be translated as &quot;okay, that's a good enough starting bid, wait an hour, okay?&quot;  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
